  "prompt": "I start talking to people with confidence but then I suddenly start fumbling mid way and become nervous,tumble upon words. How do I tackle this?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to help you maintain confidence while speaking:\n\n1. Preparation Techniques\n- Practice what you want to say beforehand\n- Have key points mentally mapped out\n- Deep breathing before conversations\n- Visualize successful interactions\n\n2. During Conversation\n- Pause and take slow, deep breaths if you feel nervous\n- Speak slower and more deliberately\n- Use natural gestures to help you feel more comfortable\n- Maintain eye contact\n- Remember that minor stammering is normal\n\n3. Mental Techniques\n- Positive self-talk\n- Challenge negative thoughts\n- Remind yourself that most people are supportive\n- Focus on the content, not your nervousness\n\n4. Skill Development\n- Practice public speaking\n- Join communication workshops\n- Consider Toastmasters\n- Take communication skills courses\n- Start with low-pressure conversations\n\n5. Physical Preparation\n- Regular exercise to reduce overall anxiety\n- Get enough sleep\n- Reduce caffeine intake\n- Practice relaxation techniques like meditation\n\n6. Professional Help\n- If anxiety is severe, consider:\n- Cognitive Behavioral Therapy\n- Speech therapy\n- Counseling for social anxiety\n\nRemember, confidence is a skill that improves with practice. Be patient with yourself.",
